+# Pala OS V10 Project Plan - 2026-06-09
+
+Status: IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_READY
+
+## 1. Goal
+
+Build Pala OS V10 as the clean final command room for local AI-assisted work.
+
+Pala OS V10 must control and verify agent work. It must not become a generic coding agent or a blind copy of old Pala OS folders.
+
+Primary user intent inferred from the local files and current conversation:
+
+- keep one final Pala OS direction,
+- use all `Codex` folder history as context,
+- preserve working V6 value,
+- avoid fake PASS,
+- make the system useful for vibe-coder workflows,
+- write evidence and reports clearly,
+- keep owner approval gates strict.
+
+## 2. Product Definition
+
+Pala OS V10 is a local-first control layer above coding/design/deploy agents.
+
+It answers these questions before and after work:
+
+- Which agent or host is allowed for this task?
+- Which standards and rules apply?
+- Which files are safe to touch?
+- Which source folders are trusted, quarantined, or reference-only?
+- Which evidence must exist before saying done?
+- Which approval gate blocks push, release, deploy, delete, import, or external writes?
+- What should the dashboard show from DB/ledger evidence only?
+
+The core law stays:
+
+```text
+Agent does the work. Pala OS verifies the work.
+```
+
+## 3. Baseline Decision
+
+Use `../pala-os-v6` as the active technical baseline.
+
+Do not use `pala-os-v10` as an empty rewrite.
+
+Do not directly merge `pala-os`, `v3`, `v4`, or `v5` into V10.
+
+Every source idea moves through this order:
+
+```text
+read -> classify -> source-card -> adapt -> test -> report -> owner gate
+```
+
+Current V6 proof:
+
+- branch: `codex/v6-source-card-gate-radar`
+- latest observed local commit: `61b5962 fix: stabilize windows test cleanup`
+- local test result: `npm.cmd test -- --test-reporter=spec` passed 38/38
+- current local dirty state: one untracked V6 plan file, `docs/v6-vibe-coder-agent-host-plan.md`
+- release posture remains `RELEASE_BLOCKED`
+
+## 4. Implementation Phases
+
+### Phase 0 - V10 Project Start
+
+Create and maintain V10 as a clean project room.
+
+Required files:
+
+- `README.md`
+- `docs/CODEX-FOLDER-READBACK-2026-06-09.md`
+- `docs/PALA-OS-V10-PROJECT-PLAN-2026-06-09.md`
+
+Acceptance:
+
+- V10 has a clear source decision.
+- V10 states that it is not executable yet.
+- No source code is copied blindly.
+- Knowledge-bank report package exists for the mutation.
+
+### Phase 1 - V10 Repo Scaffold
+
+After owner confirms implementation, initialize V10 as a real repo and create the minimum executable shell.
+
+Required baseline:
+
+- `package.json` with Node `>=24.14.0`.
+- `src/cli.js` with `sak help`, `sak status`, and `sak court`.
+- `src/config.js` with root resolution.
+- `test/pala-v10.test.js` with smoke tests.
+- `.gitignore` excluding runtime DB, logs, evidence raw files, screenshots, traces, and local secrets.
+- `AGENTS.md` carrying no-fake-done and approval gates.
+
+Acceptance:
+
+- `npm.cmd test` passes.
+- `node src/cli.js status` prints V10 status.
+- `node src/cli.js court` returns `RELEASE_BLOCKED`.
+
+### Phase 2 - V6 Core Adaptation
+
+Adapt, not bulk-copy, the proven V6 core primitives.
+
+Subsystems:
+
+- SQLite local DB and ledger.
+- 60-standard policy catalog.
+- source-card/source-court gate.
+- evidence sprint logic.
+- release court.
+- sanitized dashboard state.
+
+Acceptance:
+
+- V10 tests prove the same no-fake-done behavior as V6.
+- V10 release court cannot PASS without owner approval and evidence.
+- V10 source court marks old folders as reference/quarantine until accepted.
+
+### Phase 3 - Agent Host Matrix
+
+Make agent hosts first-class control targets.
+
+Initial hosts:
+
+- Codex
+- Cursor
+- Claude Code
+- ChatGPT
+- GitHub Copilot
+- Figma
+- GitHub
+- Vercel
+- Browser/Chrome
+- Slack
+- Google Drive
+
+Required behavior:
+
+- each host has allowed uses, blocked uses, required evidence, and approval boundary,
+- task plans name the host before implementation,
+- dashboard shows the current host state from local data.
+
+Acceptance:
+
+- `sak hosts list --json` returns host records.
+- `sak task plan "site yap" --host cursor --json` returns required rule pack and evidence.
+- No host can claim release, deploy, or product PASS by text alone.
+
+### Phase 4 - Vibe Task Router
+
+Add task planning for owner-style prompts.
+
+Task classes:
+
+- site
+- app
+- dashboard
+- API
+- CLI
+- migration
+- release
+- security review
+- design/Figma
+- data visualization
+
+Acceptance:
+
+- `sak task plan "Cursor'dan site yap" --json` produces host, standards, file boundary, evidence list, and blocked claims.
+- `sak task plan "release al" --json` returns approval-required and release-blocked.
+- `sak task plan "Figma'dan tasarimi bagla" --json` returns design evidence requirements.
+
+### Phase 5 - Dashboard Truth Surface
+
+Build only DB/ledger-backed dashboard panels.
+
+Panels:
+
+- system status,
+- court/release gate,
+- standards,
+- source cards,
+- evidence ledger,
+- agent host matrix,
+- task router,
+- environment limits,
+- operator action queue,
+- knowledge-bank report status.
+
+Acceptance:
+
+- no card turns green without evidence,
+- every card shows its source,
+- dashboard exposes local-only status before public/deploy claims,
+- visual proof is required for UI-facing PASS.
+
+### Phase 6 - Knowledge Bank Discipline
+
+Every meaningful V10 mutation produces a knowledge-bank package.
+
+Required package:
+
+- implementation report,
+- changed-files manifest,
+- repo change review,
+- raw patch/diff.
+
+Acceptance:
+
+- report package separates included files from excluded dirty files,
+- report states evidence commands,
+- report states rollback,
+- report states release posture,
+- report link is given to owner when published.
+
+## 5. Source Adoption Rules
+
+| Source | Allowed V10 use | Blocked V10 use |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `pala-os-v6` | Active baseline and adaptation source | Blind full-folder copy |
+| `pala-os-v5` | Governance and migration-court pattern | Treating old PASS as current PASS |
+| `pala-os-v3` | Method, adapter parity, no-fake-done doctrine | Runtime import without tests |
+| `pala-os-v4` | Deletion/reference audit | Making it active source |
+| `pala-os` | Legacy candidate inventory | Direct import of skills/site/MCP/CLI |
+| `konusmalar` | Memory and handoff context | Product proof or release evidence |
+| `pala-os-bilgi-bankasi` | Public report target | Release approval |
+
+## 6. Test Plan
+
+Use Windows-safe commands:
+
+```powershell
+npm.cmd test
+node src/cli.js status
+node src/cli.js court
+node src/cli.js source audit --json
+```
+
+For V6 reference checks:
+
+```powershell
+cd C:\Users\Pala-Home-1\Desktop\Codex\pala-os-v6
+npm.cmd test -- --test-reporter=spec
+```
+
+For V10 after scaffold:
+
+```powershell
+cd C:\Users\Pala-Home-1\Desktop\Codex\pala-os-v10
+npm.cmd test
+node src/cli.js court
+```
+
+Expected release result until owner approval:
+
+```text
+RELEASE_BLOCKED
+```
+
+## 7. Risks
+
+- V10 is not a Git repo yet.
+- V6 PR #1 is blocked by GitHub self-approval rules.
+- V4 has dirty tracked rule files and is behind V6.
+- Legacy `pala-os` is large and must stay quarantine/source-card only.
+- Knowledge-bank publication requires care because reports must not include secrets or raw runtime data.
+- `npm.ps1` is blocked by local PowerShell policy; use `npm.cmd`.
+
+## 8. Immediate Next Move
+
+The next implementation move should be Phase 1:
+
+```text
+Create the V10 executable scaffold with tests, court returning RELEASE_BLOCKED, and no imported legacy source.
+```
+
+Default implementation decision:
+
+- start with a small V10 scaffold,
+- keep V6 intact,
+- do not delete old folders,
+- do not push or release,
+- publish the mutation report package to the knowledge bank when owner approval for external push is explicit.
